<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%">
<tr>
	<td width="1%">&nbsp;</td>
	<td width="98%">
  
		<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%">
		<tr>
		    <td valign="top">
		     <p><font face="Verdana" size="3"><b>Article Title:</b>&nbsp;</font>
		     <font face="Verdana" size="2">Alan on pet issue's and more</font><br>
		     <a href = "../Subscribe.asp?DID=288622" ><font face="Verdana" size="2">[Subscribe to this document]</font></a></p>
			 </td>
		</tr>
		
		<tr><td>&nbsp;</tr><tr>
		
		    <td valign="top"><div style= "padding:4;float: right"> <script language=JavaScript src=http://www.obsidian-tech.com/absolutebm/abmx.aspx?z=26></script></div><p><font face="Verdana" size="2">
		    <BLockquote>

<B><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/035806.html">Pet Clarification Post (Part Two)</a></B><P>

"34 Enchanter summons a blue (animation) that has prior to yesterday's patch been able to proc a Gnoll hide Lariat. Last night I received for the first time ever in over 5 levels of using this weapon "Your pet does not have sufficient will to command this weapon". Please just give me a quick, short, and simple explanation to as why this would happen if none of the animations stats have been changed."<P>

<B>I can answer this question now. <P>

Your pets will now need to be of the appropriate level to use a procing weapon, just like a player character. It's all part of the 'procing like a PC' thing. The message is new, as is the level restriction.<P>

Alan</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

Um, Absor... He used a level 34 summoning spell and got a Blue pet. Gnoll Hide Lariat procs at 25 if I remember correctly.<P>

<B>Oi!<P>

Yer right.<P>

I'll look into it further...<P>

Yup, that seems to be the case. It is definitely possible for the 34th level spell to summon a pet that can't proc with that weapon.<P>

Alan</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

wow ! they locked my thread minutes after i posted it ! It was mostly for humour, but some truth in it, because..... PETS CANNOT HIT THEIR TARGETS ! man, how long do we have to spam like this ? pets hitting for less than 50% and they completely ignore the paying costomer?<P>

<B>DooMeous,<P>

Despite popular belief, the volume of spamming about this issue is not going to change how we react to it.<P>

The number of intelligent posts with new and useful information will most certainly have an effect on how we react.<P>

But spamming just to repeat yourself and vent is not something that helps you, or me.<P>

I've seen several posts on mage specific sites from mages saying that nothing is different besides the procing and dual wielding changes...<P>

*shrug*<P>

Alan</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

Sinrakin wrote: "Absor - communication is a two way street. If you're going to lock every thread about pets, then please address the question. Would you please summarize your current understanding of the pet situation, and why the observations of so many thousands of people appear to disagree with Verant's claim that pets were not changed to make them hit less often?"<P>

<B>Well, I've done so in this very thread. I'll gladly do it again.<P>

My understanding is that we only changed the rate of pet procing with weapons and their ability to dual wield without weapons. Nothing more.<P>

Your claim that thousands of people disagree is a bit exaggerated. I do see, however, a lot of people disagreeing with my understanding. And I've read a lot of posts on mage specific boards (where there seems to be less pressure to spam…) that say that pets are not hitting less or being hit more or harder.<P>

This does not mean that I am ignoring your concerns.<P>

Keep in mind something, though. Pets will do less damage without the massive procing they were doing before. This means that their opponents will remain fighting longer, won't run as early and won't die as soon. So the pet will be more likely to die. Also keep in mind that most people don't really pay that much attention to the details of their pets combat (many mages sit out of message range while their pets fight, and others have their misses off). New attention to these details might very well make pets seem weaker where they may not be.<P>

While I gladly accept that some of you perceive your pets to be missing more, I also have to accept that others perceive that they are not.<P>

I continue to read your posts, and I continue to look into this matter. But for now I have no new information to offer, and I thought you all would be tired of hearing me restate my understanding over and over again. I will certainly let you know if I learn something new.<P>

Alan</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<B><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/035959.html">this board is out of control!</a></B><P>

I know a lot of mage, pet and my class sucks, grips that need to be locked and deleted off this board.
Also all the why wont verant respond posts to that dont have what Verant is supposed to respond to?<P>

<B>Alright...<P>

So now I have to go from locking post about pets, to locking posts about the posts about pets...<P>

*sigh*<P>

Alan</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<B><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/035984.html">Bug? Problem? - Entering World (not responding)</a></B><P>

Anyone else have this problem or anything close to it? Since this last patch I have been experiencing a where EnteringWorld locks and task manager tells me it is not responding. I log in, choose my server, select my character, the loading screen picture comes up (Iksar and chicky babe), then it goes blank and just sits there.<P>

<B>A thorough file check is the first step in fixing something like this, especially since it's pretty easy to do. :)<P>

But in general you're better off posting your technical problems on our tech support board. David does a great job helping people with their technical problems.<P>

Alan</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<B><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/036021.html">Why does thread after thread about Useless pets go unanswered?</a></B><P>

We use a mage pet as our primary tank most of the time, and now, well, we cant. A level 51 earth pet is now a shadow of its former self. This is fact, it cannot in any way be denied. They made pets much worse, and now they will not even talk to people about it, i don't understand. I have a chardok raid going on tonight, and we just lost a huge chunk of our offense and defense with this nerf.<P>

<B>Unfortunately, I am locking threads again. It's not very useful to any of us that are actually trying to discuss this issue to have to hunt for information. If we stick to one location we'll be able to talk about it much more easily. And this board isn't as useful if the front page is full of post on one topic.<P>

Alan</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<B><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/036031.html">For heavens sake. You locked the Test Server thread?</a></B><P>

Folks know the history of the Test server......why in heavens did you feel the need to lock that?<P>

<B>Yup. I am only locking pet threads to keep the board open for you to talk about other things, like the Test Server, if you want. And mages would be better served posting in one thread, it makes it much easier for me to read and respond.<P>

Alan</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<B><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/036034.html">Why did you lock my thread?</a></B><P>

CMON! This is crazy!!  WTH is this?? All we want is a tidbit or a simple, 'Hey, we are looking into it' Is that too much to ask??<P>

<B>Secias,<P>

I'm locking the extraneous threads about pets. I'm doing it because some of you are forcing me to do it, and because I want to converse with people about it, not hunt down individual posts.<P>

And now, because I'm wasting my time locking threads, I'm going to ask you to stop posting more threads like this one. Please. I'm not inclined toward sending warnings…<P>

Alan</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<B><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/036039.html">My complaint about Verant Interactive</a></B><P>

Writing this letter stems from a desperation to be heard, if not by a court of law, then by a court of public opinion. Before I start,
however, I should state that to understand what Verant Interactive's particularly saturnine form of jujuism has encompassed as a
movement and as a system of rule, we have to look at its historical context and development as a form of lawless politics that first
arose in early twentieth-century Europe in response to rapid social upheaval, the devastation of World War I, and the Bolshevik
Revolution. <P>

<B>Now why would I lock this?<P>

I have a pretty good eye for sarcasm when I see it.<P>

And an even better eye for random rant generators. The real giveaway is the shear length of the post... :)<P>

Alan</B>
</blockquote>
		    </font></p>
